"v.传授，告知 【英】 v. 传授，告知(to make known; tell; reveal) 【记】 im(进入)+part(部份) →成为(知识)一部份 →告知 【例】 The good teacher imparts wisdom to his pupils. v. 传授, 告知, 透露 = reveal = disclose 【记】im进入, part部份－成为你的一部份－告知你一件事情 【根】part分享－分享事情－传授 【记】im + part 部份，我有很多份，给出去一部份 impart (v.)  early 15c., ""to give a part of (one's possessions); late 15c., ""to share, take part,"" from Old French impartir (14c.), from Late Latin impartire (also impertire) ""to share in, divide with another, communicate,"" from assimilated form of in- ""into, in"" (see in- (2)) + partire ""to divide, part"" (see part (v.)). Related: Imparted; imparting."
